{"ts":"2026-06-24T23:17:49.163Z","author":"claude-code-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-mthy"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"Add pm package / pm packages shell completion (bash/zsh/fish), including the package-only --declarative flag"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"src/cli/commands/completion.ts only emits a lifecycle completion block for `pm extension` (bash `extension)` case, zsh `extension)` case, fish `__fish_seen_subcommand_from extension`). There is NO completion block for `pm package` / `pm packages`, so the package lifecycle command (the primary package-mode authoring entry per docs/SDK.md) has never had shell completion. Surfaced in PR #359 review (Gemini): after scoping `--declarative` to package mode, it was removed from the extension completion (correct — `pm extension init` no longer accepts it) but there is no package completion to carry it. Fix: add `package`/`packages` lifecycle completion blocks mirroring the extension block across bash/zsh/fish, including the package-only `--declarative` flag, and assert them in completion-command.spec.ts. Pre-existing gap, scoped out of #359 to keep that PR focused on the declarative capability matrix."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Task"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":3},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["area:cli","area:packages","dx","follow-up"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-06-24T23:17:49.163Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-24T23:17:49.163Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"claude-code-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-ugqx"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"aa2625568d142983a1b497790a176de95fa6ab415eac7bfe46090947f35139ae","message":""}
